      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds were controlled within ±1% of target values. Blood surrogate properties were characterised at test temperature. However, outlet pressure boundary conditions were set to time-averaged values without capturing pulsatility present in the VAD operating environment, reducing equivalency. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel, area validation metric) computed with combined experimental and simulation uncertainty bands at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Relative error was computed at all five points. Combined uncertainty intervals were propagated from Monte Carlo UQ but experimental uncertainty on NIH measurements was characterised only as inter-sample standard deviation without accounting for systematic laboratory bias. Formal validation metric per ASME V&V 20 not applied. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
